  <title>Products of Topological Spaces</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the product of a finite number of topological spaces?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we define a topology on the product of a finite number of topological spaces?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is a projection map from a product of a finite number of topological spaces?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How can we use projection maps to determine the continuity of a function to a product of a finite number of topological spaces?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is a subbasis of a topological space?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What properties do product spaces inherit from their factors?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
